      • setShouldLoadPreview

        public void setShouldLoadPreview(boolean shouldLoadPreview)
        Description copied from interface: GfycatPlayer
        If set to true preview image will be loaded and displayed while larger animated file is being loaded.

        Default value is false.

        IMPORTANT: Call this method before GfycatPlayer.setupGfycat(Gfycat), otherwise preview image will not be loaded.

        Note: Use FrameSequenceView#setupPreview(Drawable, boolean) instead if you need to display your own preview.

        You can also download preview image manually and set it as a preview with FrameSequenceView#setupPreview(Drawable, boolean) if you already have one, or there are other needs.

        Specified by:
        setShouldLoadPreview in interface GfycatPlayer

      • setupPreview

        public void setupPreview(android.graphics.drawable.Drawable drawable,
                         boolean animate)
        Description copied from interface: GfycatPlayer
        Set preview manually by calling this method.

        Note: If GfycatPlayer.setShouldLoadPreview(boolean) is set to true then preview image will be replaced by the one loaded from FrameSequenceSource#loadPoster().

        Specified by:
        setupPreview in interface GfycatPlayer
        Parameters:
        drawable - to use as preview, until actual animation will be loaded is being loaded.
        animate - set to true if transition animation needed.
